     <td valign=top width=470>                                                              


      <center>
      <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width=475>
	    <tr>
         <td style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 10pt;" background="/images/bg_heading_blue_01.jpg"><center><b>The Passing of Cros</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		 <td>                            
	                                   

	    <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
		  <tr><td><font color="00dd00">Submitted by:</td><td><font color="00dd00">Trior</td></tr>
        </table>
	  <br>
	  <br>


          Two Eves hence there was a great tragedy in the Qeynos hills.  It seems Cros, a great and brave Ranger was slain by the mate of Mammoth.  This bear was afflicted with a horrible curse, the very same that seems to be plagueing our lands.  This true and kind servant of Tunare died at the maw of the very one he protected. Protector Holy gave a touching ceremony in his honor outside of Surefall Glade at dawn.  From those attending she chose a few to bear torches high and speak words to of rememberance.  I was one of those who spoke.<br>
          <br>
          We will remember Cros, and his loss will touch all of Norrath. It is a sign of dark times when such a great man can fall in such a tragic way. This curse can go on no longer. We must find its source and we must crush it.  <br>
          <br>
          I am Trior, an acolyte in the Temple of Karana and a faithful member of the Birds of Prey.  We who bear the Hammer of our god seek vengeance for our fallen comrade in arms.  The forces of nature will rebute!  Cros's death shall not be in vain. <br>
          <br>
          I bid you take up arms and join my brethren and I in discovering and routing this darkness.  Let this madness end!<br>
          <br>
          Trior<br>
          Cleric of Karana<br>
          Birds of Prey<br>
          <br>
          OOC:<br>
          <br>
          This was a GM event where proof of Cros's death had to be found, and then a funeral was held.  At the funeral about 6 people were chosen to bare torches and say a few words in his honor.  During this event a strang NPC appeared, a woman who grew very large and then vanished.  We are not sure if it was related.  Gifts were given to those who spoke in his name.  I personally was given 150gp, which is not bad for a 2nd level character.  <br>
          <br>
          Thank you to the GMs of Prexus.  This was a fantastic event and we will love many more such roleplaying situations.  I have been playing this game for 6 months and this was my first GM event.  I thought it was great.  I have heard a lot of mention of events occuring that focus on RP skill rather than fighting skill and I think it is a great improvement in the game.<br>
          <br>
          Glad to be a part.  <br>
          <br>
          Kalose Drekmordan(22 Warrior) / Trior (2 Cleric)<br>
          Birds of Prey Guild<br>
          Prexus Server<br>
          </td>
		 </tr>
